definition: to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send

sentences.english: A Confederate boat carried Fox to Sumter.
sentences.chinese: 一艘邦聯的船隻將福克斯運送到薩姆特堡。

sentences.english: These ignition wires send the charge to each spark plug.
sentences.chinese: 這些點火導線將電荷運送至每個火花塞。

sentences.english: Wow he send weapons to the enemy who beheads Christians.
sentences.chinese: 哇他竟然給斬殺基督徒的敵人運送武器。

sentences.english: Moving the metal is like 'a big military operation, ' he says.
sentences.chinese: 他說，運送黃金就像一場大規模的軍事行動。

sentences.english: The fringelike fimbriae transport ovulated eggs from the ovarian surface to the infundibulum.
sentences.chinese: 花邊狀的傘將排出的卵，從卵巢表面運送到漏斗。

sentences.english: A truck brings in a delivery in through a wide, slow-moving gate.
sentences.chinese: 一輛卡車通過一扇寬闊的緩慢開啓的大門運送物資。

sentences.english: Great supplies were sent to the disaster-hit area.
sentences.chinese: 大量的給養被運送到遭受災難襲擊的地區。

sentences.english: This then allows for direct shipments and eliminates transshipping of the product.
sentences.chinese: 這樣就可以直接裝船運送產品，而不需轉船。

sentences.english: As it is mainly for goods transportation the interior seems lousy.
sentences.chinese: 而基於它主要用作運送貨物，內寵就顯得凌亂。

sentences.english: Most fruit is sent overseas by airfreight in order to save time.
sentences.chinese: 大部分運送到海外的水果都是用空運以節省時間。

sentences.english: By the 16th century, skaters were transporting goods across frozen waterways.
sentences.chinese: 16世紀的溜冰者是在冰凍的水面上運送貨物。

sentences.english: But getting food to Fort Sumter would be a very difficult job.
sentences.chinese: 但要向薩姆特堡運送給養卻是一件非常困難的事。

sentences.english: As soon as a tuna is sold at auction, it is hauled off to the buyer's stall by cart.
sentences.chinese: 一旦金槍魚拍賣成功，就會由卡車運送到買家的貨攤。

sentences.english: Traditionally, eight people carry in the flag at the Opening Ceremony.
sentences.chinese: 傳統上，在開幕典禮上會有八個人運送旗幟進入會場。

sentences.english: If the drought continues, water deliveries to Arizona could potentially be cut back.
sentences.chinese: 如果幹旱持續，運送到亞利桑那州的水可能會削減。

sentences.english: Therefore, two channels were placed underneath the switchboard to facilitate the sliding motion.
sentences.chinese: 因此，工人將兩條長角鐵置於配電箱底部，方便運送。

definition: to procure (for an enterprise etc)/to purchase
to carry (on one's person)/to support (old)/Taiwan pr. [xi1 dai4]
